column1: Joke
The train conductor was always on track with his plans.
The rotation of Earth really makes my day.
The minus sign was talking to the positive sign. The minus sign asked, “Are you sure I make a difference?” and the other sign said “I’m positive!”
The man who invented Velcro has died. RIP.
The man who invented knock-knock jokes should get a no bell prize.
The first time I got a universal remote control, I thought to myself, ‘This changes everything.’
The future, the present, and the past walk into a bar. Things got a little tense.
The bicycle couldn't stand up by itself; it was two-tired.
I have a quantum mechanics joke. It's both funny and not funny at the same time.

Einstein, Newton and Pascal decide to play hide and seek. Einstein is it, closes his eyes, counts to 10 then opens them. Pascal is nowhere to be seen. Newton is sitting right in front of Einstein, with a piece of chalk in his hand. He's sitting in a box drawn on the ground, a meter to a side. Einstein says 'Newton, you're terrible, I've found you!' Newton says 'No no, Einy. You've found one Newton per square meter. You've found Pascal!
Four fonts walk into a bar. The bartender says, ‘Hey! We don’t want your type in here!’
How can you tell if an engineer's an extrovert? When he's talking with you, he looks at your shoes instead of his own.
How do electricians greet each other? “Watt’s up?”
How do electricians stay fit? By doing alternating current exercises.
How does a mathematician get Tan? Sin/Cos
How do you make a tissue dance? You put a little boogie in it. :)
Wind turbine 1: "What kind of music do you like?" Wind turbine 2:  "I'm a big metal fan"
Will glass coffins be a success? Remains to be seen.
Why was the mobile phone wearing glasses? Because it lost its contacts.
Why was the mobile phone wearing glasses? Because it lost its contacts.
Why should you never invest in bakeries? Because they have a high turnover rate.
Why doesn't the sun need to go to University? It's too bright.
Why does a chicken coop have two doors? Because if it had four it would be a chicken sedan!
Why do they make Raisin Bran commercials? For raisin bran awareness.
Why do Hobbits have to wear shoes now? Because a new Lego store was just opened in the Shire.
Why do electricians resolve issues quickly? They’re always current on solutions.
Why do electricians never panic? They always stay grounded.
Why do cicadas stay up all night chirping irregularly, unable to sleep? Their cicadan rhythm is off
Why didn't the baby oyster share her little pearl? She was a little shellfish.
Why did the traffic engineer install a disco ball at the intersection? To keep the flow upbeat.
Why did the traffic engineer cross the road? To conduct a thorough pedestrian analysis.
Why did the traffic engineer become a stand-up comedian? To prove that timing is everything.
Why did the puppy get away with committing murder? ...He had paws-able deniability.
Why did the programmer quit his job? Because he didn't get arrays.
Why did the PowerPoint presentation cross the road? To get to the other slide.
Why did the mortgage broker go out of business? ...because he lost interest.
Why did the golfer bring two pairs of pants? In case he got a hole in one.
Why did the engineering students leave class early? They were getting a little ANSI.
Why did the electrician couple break up? There was no spark left.
Why did the electrician bring a backup battery? In case of a shocking emergency.
Why did the programer become so poor? Because he used up all his cache.
Why did the cyclist get recognized? For pedaling bright ideas.
Why did the computer arrive late at work? Because it had a hard drive.
Why did the circle get offended by the triangle? Because the triangle looked at the circle and said “You’re pointless!”
Why did the chef invest in chicken and cow bones? He wanted to buy stock options.
Why did the banker leave his job? He lost interest.
Why did the air freshener company go out of business? Because they lacked common scents...
Why can’t your nose grow to be 12 inches long? Because then it would be a foot.
Who's bad at baseball but fun at parties? A pitcher filled with margaritas!
Whiteboards are remarkable.
Where do snowmen dance? At the snowball!
When the cannibal showed up late to the buffet, they gave him the cold shoulder.
When I come to work I like to find a really good hiding place... Good employees are hard to find! -Darren
What's the difference between civil engineers and mechanical engineers? Mechanical engineers build missiles, civil engineers build targets.
What's it called if a mosquito bit a hobbit 8 times? A mosquito byte!
What's green, fuzzy, and if it falls out of a tree it'll kill you? A pool table.
What’s the difference between ignorance and apathy? I don’t know and I don’t care.
What’s the difference between a doctor and an engineer? A doctor kills people one at a time.
What’s an engineer’s favorite tool? A perfectly calibrated pun.
What’s an electrician’s favorite exercise? Circuit training.
What’s a traffic engineer’s favorite snack? Asphalt chips with dip.
What’s a traffic engineer’s favorite music genre? Heavy Traffic Metal.
What was the spider doing on the computer? Making a web-site
What kind of birds stick together? Vel-crows
What is the difference between a Siberian husky and an Alaskan husky? About 1500 miles.
What is the difference between a City Manager and the Pope? You only have to kiss the Pope's ring.
What if there were no hypothetical questions?
What has more letters than the alphabet? The post office.
What happens to a frog's car when it breaks down? It gets toad away.
What does Steve Jobs like to order from McDonald's? A big Mac
What does a subatomic duck say? Quark!
What do you give an electrician for their birthday? Shorts.
What do you get when you cross an octopus with a cow? A stern rebuke from the Ethics Committee, and an immediate cessation of funding.
What do you do if a cow is in the middle of the road you're driving on? steer clear
What do you call apes who share an Amazon account? Prime mates.
What do you call an electrician who tries to work as a carpenter? A bad electrician. What do you call a carpenter who tries to work as an electrician? A dead carpenter.
What do you call an atheist bone? A blasfemur.
What do you call an alien in a swamp? A MARSHian
What do you call a truthful piece of paper? Fax.
What do you call a nose without a body? Nobody knows...
What do you call a loaf baked in a zoo? Bread in captivity.
What do you call a fake noodle? An Impasta
What do you call a cow that just gave birth? Decaffeinated
What do you call a camel in Alaska? Lost.
What do nuclear engineers like to eat? Fission chips
What do gingerbread men use to walk when they break their legs? Candy canes.
What do engineers use for birth control? Their personalities.
Why did Episodes 4, 5, and 6 come out before 1, 2, and 3? Because in charge of directing, Yoda was. May the Fourth be with you this week!
What did the traffic engineer say to a malfunctioning signal? “You’re sending mixed signals!”
What did the structural engineer say to the architect? Nice buttress.
What did the pebble say to the rock? I wish I was a little boulder!
What did the mama cow say to the baby cow? It's pasture bedtime!
What did the grape say when it got crushed? Nothing, it just let out a little wine.
What did the farmer say when he lost his tractor? Where's my tractor?
What did the electrician say to cheer up a friend? “Don't resist – you have great potential!”
What did the electrician proclaim at the power station? “I’m amped about this job!”
What did Tennessee? What Arkansas.
What did batman say to robin before robin got in the car? get in the car
Wanna hear two short jokes and a long joke? Joke joke jooooke!
Two wifi engineers got married. The reception was fantastic.
Two antennas met on a roof, fell in love and got married. The ceremony wasn't great, but the reception was excellent!
To estimate how long a project will take, add up the time required for each task and multiple the sum by pi. That ensures that all your budgets will be irrational!
This dermatologist waits a month to diagnose a skin disorder... She's reluctant to make a rash decision.
They told me I had type "A" blood... turns out it was a typo.

There was a Doctor, an Engineer, and a Planner discussing which was the oldest profession. The Doctor pointed out that God created Eve from Adam's rib. This obviously required surgery, so therefore that was the oldest profession in the world. The Engineer countered prior to that stated that God created order from the chaos, and that was most certainly the biggest and best engineering example ever, proving his profession was the oldest. The Planner leaned back in her chair, and with a sly smile responded, "Yes, but who do you think created the chaos?"
What do gingerbread men use to walk when they break their legs? Candy canes.
What do you call a greedy elf? ... Elfish!
What do you call an obnoxious reindeer? Rude-olph.
What's a Christmas tree's favorite candy? Orna-mints!
Why did the Christmas tree go to the barber? It needed to be trimmed.
What happened to the turkey that got in a fight? He got the stuffing knocked out of him!
Why did the farmer separate the chicken from the turkey? Suspected fowl play!
The easiest time to add insult to injury is when you’re signing someone’s cast.
The definition of ultimate silliness? 100 urban planners in 1 room.
Did you hear about the skeleton who didn't go to prom? He had no body to go with.
The barman says, “We don’t serve time travelers in here.” A time traveler walks into a bar. -Raymond
Some random variables were talking in a bar. They thought they were being discrete but their chatter was continuous.
So Sherlock... asked Watson, "I forget, what was your highest degree of education?" "Elementary, my dear Watson."
Refusing to go to the gym is a form of resistance training.
DUDE: Developer Under Delusions of Entitlement
BANANA: Build Absolutely Nothing Anywhere Near Anything
AICP: Any Idiot Can Plan
Planners' Dictionary
One of the cows didn’t produce milk today. It was an udder failure.
One fifth of people... ...are just too tense!

On a traffic light, green means 'go' and yellow means 'yield', but on a banana it's just the opposite. Green means 'hold on', yellow means 'go ahead,' and red means 'where the hell did you get that banana?" - Mitch Hedberg

Never ask a mechanic to perform surgery because they’ll try to turn the patient off before they start. And never ask a medical doctor for car advice because if your engine is making loud noises they’ll just write you a prescription for ear plugs.
Never ask a database administrator to help you move because they might drop your tables.
My wife told me to stop impersonating a flamingo. I had to put my foot down.
My teachers told me I'd never amount to much because I procrastinate so much. I told them, "Just you wait!"
My least favorite engineering class was statics. It was dull, but it did have its moments.
My grandpa started walking five miles a day when he was 60... Now hes 97 years old and we have no idea where he is...
My grandma refused to be an organ donor. She was buried with all of her musical instruments.
My friend’s bakery burned down last night. Now his business is toast.
My friend was explaining electricity to me, but I was like, ‘Watt?’
Most people are shocked when they find out how bad I am as an electrician.
Maybe if we start telling people their brain is an app, they’ll want to use it.
Knock knock Who's there? Abby. Abby who. A bee has stolen my wallet.
Just got fired from my job as a set designer. I left without making a scene.
I'm naming my TV remote Waldo... ...for obvious reasons.
I'll do algebra, I'll do trig, and I'll even do statistics. But graphing is where I draw the line.
If you don’t pay your exorcist, do you get repossessed?
If it wasn't for physics I'd be unstopable.
If attacked by a mob of clowns, go for the juggler.
If a parsley farmer gets sued, can they garnish his wages?
I went to a seafood disco last week, and ended up pulling a mussel.
I was addicted to the hokey pokey but I turned myself around.
I used to think I was indecisive. But now I’m not so sure.
I threw a boomerang a couple years ago; I know live in constant fear.
I saw a great movie about databases today. I can't wait for the SQL.
The roundest knight at Sir Arthur’s table was Sir Cumference. He ate too much pi. Happy Pi Day!
I have a joke about deep learning but I can't explain it.
I have a geography joke, but I don't know where it is.
I had a teacher named Mr Gandalf once, nobody passed his class.
I got a new pair of gloves today, but they’re both ‘lefts,’ which on the one hand is great, but on the other, it’s just not right.
I feed my cat lemons. He's a real sour puss.
I didn’t think orthopedic shoes would help, but I stand corrected.
I can tell when people are being judgmental just by looking at them.
I buy all my guns from a guy called T-Rex. He’s a small arms dealer.

How many urban planners does it take to change a light bulb? At least four: One to change the bulb, another to say that the third person should have been consulted before the change, and a fourth to organize a community meeting to discuss the cultural and societal impacts of the new bulb.
What does a caterpillar do on January 1? Turns over a new leaf.
How much does Santa pay for parking? Nothing, it's on the house
What's the perfect stocking stuffer? A foot…
Why does everyone love Frosty the Snowman...? Because he's cool!
How do electricians fix a broken romance? They rewire the connection.
My friends told me to stop telling Thanksgiving jokes, but I couldn't quit cold turkey.
Have you heard about the new restaurant called ‘Karma?’ There’s no menu—you get what you deserve.
Geology rocks, but geography’s where it’s at.
Gandalf was very unhappy at work. He couldn't find his staff!
A ghost walked into a bar and ordered a shot of vodka. The bartender said, ‘Sorry, we don’t serve spirits here.’
Why did the ghost go into the bar? For the Boos.
Did you take a shower today? Why, is one missing?
What do you call 8 hobbits? A hobbyte.
Did you hear about the guy whose whole left side got amputated? He’s all right now.
Did you hear about the guy who fell into an upholstery machine? Now he's fully recovered.
Despite the high cost of living, it remains popular.
Dancing trees? Now that's ENT-ertainment.
My son took Rock Climbing in college but he had to drop the class. He couldn't find any "Cliff Notes."
Coarse Aggregate says: 'Hey Sand, how are you?' Sand replies: 'I’m fine.'
Blunt pencils are really pointless.
Before you criticize someone, walk a mile in their shoes. That way, when you do criticize them, you’re a mile away and you have their shoes.
Ask your doctor if left is right for you.
Artificial intelligence is no match for natural stupidity
Are people born with photographic memories, or does it take time to develop?
An indeterminate beam walks into a bar. "What can I get ya?" asks the bartender. "Just give me a moment," replies the beam.
Alcohol and calculus never mix. Don't drink and derive!
Albert Einstein developed a theory about space. And it was about time, too!
A uniform beam walks into a bar. The barman asks: 'What would you like, sir?' The beam replies: 'Ummm… just give me a moment.'
A three-legged dog walks into a saloon in the Old West. He slides up to the bar and announces: ''I'm looking for the man who shot my paw.''  Courtesy of Daniel Fine
A termite walks into the bar and asks, ‘Is the bar tender here?’
A Photon checks into a hotel and the receptionist asks if he needs any help with his luggage. “No thanks,” says the Photon “I’m travelling light.”

A man is flying in a hot air balloon and realizes he is lost. He reduces height and spots a man down below. He lowers the balloon further and shouts: 'Excuse me, can you help me? I promised my friend I would meet him half an hour ago, but I don't know where I am.' The man below says: 'Yes. You are in a hot air balloon, hovering approximately 30 feet above this field.' 'You must be an engineer,' says the balloonist. 'I am,' replies the man. 'How did you know?' 'Well,' says the balloonist, 'everything you have told me is technically correct, but I have no idea what to make of your information.' The man below says, 'You must be a planner.' 'I am,' replies the balloonist, 'but how did you know?' 'Well,' says the man, 'you don't know where you are, or where you are going, and you have made a promise which you have no idea how to keep.'
A hobbit was not watching where he was going and he bumped into the wizard. He said, "Saruman, didn't see you there"!
A dung beetle walks into a bar and asks, ‘Is this stool taken?’
6:30 is the best time on a clock, hands down.

An advertisement for a car school claimed it could teach anyone to drive a car in five minutes or less. A man called them up and asked, 'How can you teach anyone to drive in five minutes or less?' They answered. 'It's a crash course.'
